testcase.name: Update personal details in my profile
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag2 Scenario: Update personal details in my profile # Features/Account Management (client).feature:15 Given I am logged in as a Client When I update my personal details such as age and fitness goals Then my updated personal details should be saved successfully in my profile

testcase.name: Set dietary preferences in my profile
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag3 Scenario: Set dietary preferences in my profile # Features/Account Management (client).feature:23 Given I am logged in as a Client When I set my dietary preferences or restrictions (e.g., vegetarian, gluten-free) Then my dietary preferences should be saved successfully in my profile

testcase.name: Edit dietary preferences or restrictions
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag4 Scenario: Edit dietary preferences or restrictions # Features/Account Management (client).feature:31 Given I am logged in as a Client When I edit my dietary preferences or restrictions (e.g., add lactose intolerance) Then my edited dietary preferences should be updated successfully in my profile

testcase.name: View personal details and dietary preferences
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag5 Scenario: View personal details and dietary preferences # Features/Account Management (client).feature:39 Given I am logged in as a Client When I view my profile Then I should be able to see my personal details, fitness goals, and dietary preferences

testcase.name: Attempt to create a profile with invalid details
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag6 Scenario: Attempt to create a profile with invalid details # Features/Account Management (client).feature:48 Given I am logged in as a Client When I attempt to create a profile with invalid details such as age = "abc" Then I should see an error message indicating invalid input And my profile should not be saved

testcase.name: Attempt to create a profile with missing mandatory details
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag7 Scenario: Attempt to create a profile with missing mandatory details # Features/Account Management (client).feature:57 Given I am logged in as a Client When I attempt to create a profile without providing my age Then I should see an error message indicating that age is required And my profile should not be saved

testcase.name: Delete my profile
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag8 Scenario: Delete my profile # Features/Account Management (client).feature:66 Given I am logged in as a Client When I choose to delete my profile Then my profile should be removed from the system And I should no longer be able to access my account

testcase.name: Unauthorized access to another client's profile
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag9 Scenario: Unauthorized access to another client's profile # Features/Account Management (client).feature:75 Given I am logged in as a Client When I attempt to access another client's profile Then I should receive an error message indicating insufficient permissions And I should not be able to view or edit their profile

testcase.name: Approve New Instructor
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag1 Scenario: Approve New Instructor # Features/ApproveinstructorFeature.feature:7 Given I am logged in as an admin And there is a pending instructor registration When I review the registration details And I approve the new instructor registration Then the instructor should be added to the system as an active user And I should see a success message confirming the approval

testcase.name: Reject New Instructor
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag2 Scenario: Reject New Instructor # Features/ApproveinstructorFeature.feature:18 Given I am logged in as an admin And there is a pending instructor registration When I review the registration details And I reject the new instructor registration Then the instructor should not be added to the system And I should see a rejection message confirming the action

testcase.name: View Pending Instructor Registrations
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag3 Scenario: View Pending Instructor Registrations # Features/ApproveinstructorFeature.feature:29 Given I am logged in as an admin When I navigate to the "Pending Registrations" section Then I should see a list of all pending instructor registrations And I should be able to review the details of each registration

testcase.name: Notify Instructor After Approval
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag4 Scenario: Notify Instructor After Approval # Features/ApproveinstructorFeature.feature:38 Given I am logged in as an admin And I approve a new instructor registration When the registration is approved Then the instructor should receive a notification email confirming their approval And I should see a message confirming the email has been sent

testcase.name: Notify Instructor After Rejection
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag5 Scenario: Notify Instructor After Rejection # Features/ApproveinstructorFeature.feature:48 Given I am logged in as an admin And I reject a new instructor registration When the registration is rejected Then the instructor should receive a notification email about the rejection And I should see a message confirming the rejection email has been sent

testcase.name: Approve a Submitted Fitness Tip
testcase.system-out: Scenario: Approve a Submitted Fitness Tip # Features/ContentManagement.feature:5 Given I am logged in as an admin When I approve a submitted fitness tip titled "5-Minute Stretching Routine" Then the tip "5-Minute Stretching Routine" should be publicly visible on the platform

testcase.name: Reject a Submitted Fitness Tip
testcase.system-out: Scenario: Reject a Submitted Fitness Tip # Features/ContentManagement.feature:10 Given I am logged in as an admin When I reject a submitted fitness tip titled "5-Minute Stretching Routine" with reason "Lack of sufficient details" Then the submitter should receive a notification "Lack of sufficient details" And the tip "5-Minute Stretching Routine" should not be publicly visible

testcase.name: Delete a Publicly Visible Fitness Tip
testcase.system-out: Scenario: Delete a Publicly Visible Fitness Tip # Features/ContentManagement.feature:16 Given I am logged in as an admin And the fitness tip "Beginner Yoga Postures" is publicly visible When I delete the fitness tip "Beginner Yoga Postures" Then the tip "Beginner Yoga Postures" should no longer be visible on the platform

testcase.name: View Feedback for a Fitness Tip
testcase.system-out: Scenario: View Feedback for a Fitness Tip # Features/ContentManagement.feature:22 Given I am logged in as an admin When I view feedback for the fitness tip titled "Home Workout Plan" Then I should see all user comments and ratings for "Home Workout Plan"

testcase.name: Remove Inappropriate Feedback
testcase.system-out: Scenario: Remove Inappropriate Feedback # Features/ContentManagement.feature:27 Given I am logged in as an admin And there is a feedback comment "Inappropriate language" on the fitness tip titled "Healthy Morning Routine" When I remove the inappropriate feedback on "Healthy Morning Routine" Then the feedback should no longer be visible under the "Healthy Morning Routine" tip

testcase.name: Respond to a Feedback Question
testcase.system-out: Scenario: Respond to a Feedback Question # Features/ContentManagement.feature:33 Given I am logged in as an admin And there is a feedback question "Can I do this routine with back pain?" on the fitness tip "5-Minute Stretching Routine" When I respond to the feedback with "Please consult a physician before attempting." Then my response should be visible under the feedback question

testcase.name: Rate a completed program
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag1 Scenario: Rate a completed program # Features/FeedbackandReviews(client).feature:7 Given I have completed a program When I rate the program with a score of 5 stars Then the rating should be saved successfully And I should be able to view my rating on the program page

testcase.name: Write a review for a completed program
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag2 Scenario: Write a review for a completed program # Features/FeedbackandReviews(client).feature:16 Given I have completed a program When I write a review with the content "Great program, helped me lose weight" Then the review should be saved successfully And I should be able to view my review on the program page

testcase.name: Submit a suggestion for improvement to an instructor
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag3 Scenario: Submit a suggestion for improvement to an instructor # Features/FeedbackandReviews(client).feature:25 Given I have completed a program When I submit a suggestion with the content "Would love to have more flexibility in the schedule" Then the suggestion should be saved successfully And the instructor should be notified of my suggestion

testcase.name: View all ratings and reviews for a completed program
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag4 Scenario: View all ratings and reviews for a completed program # Features/FeedbackandReviews(client).feature:34 Given I have completed a program When I view the program page Then I should be able to see all ratings and reviews from other clients

testcase.name: Edit my review for a completed program
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag5 Scenario: Edit my review for a completed program # Features/FeedbackandReviews(client).feature:42 Given I have completed a program And I have already written a review When I edit my review to change the content to "Excellent program, very helpful" Then my review should be updated successfully And I should be able to see the updated review on the program page

testcase.name: Submit a negative or inappropriate rating
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag6 Scenario: Submit a negative or inappropriate rating # Features/FeedbackandReviews(client).feature:52 Given I have completed a program When I rate the program with a score of 1 star and a comment "Terrible, didn't help me at all" Then the rating should be flagged for review by the system And I should be notified that my rating is under review

testcase.name: Write an inappropriate review
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag7 Scenario: Write an inappropriate review # Features/FeedbackandReviews(client).feature:61 Given I have completed a program When I write a review with content "This program was garbage!" Then the review should be flagged as inappropriate And I should be notified that my review has been rejected due to inappropriate content

testcase.name: Submit a duplicate review or rating
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag8 Scenario: Submit a duplicate review or rating # Features/FeedbackandReviews(client).feature:69 Given I have already rated a program with 5 stars When I try to submit the same 5-star rating again Then I should be informed that I have already rated this program And the system should not allow the duplicate rating or review

testcase.name: Submit an incomplete or vague review
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag9 Scenario: Submit an incomplete or vague review # Features/FeedbackandReviews(client).feature:78 Given I have completed a program When I submit a review with the content "Good program" Then the system should prompt me to provide more details if the review is too vague And the review should not be saved until I provide a more detailed review

testcase.name: Admin review of ratings and reviews before publishing
testcase.system-out: @tag @tag10 Scenario: Admin review of ratings and reviews before publishing # Features/FeedbackandReviews(client).feature:87 Given I have submitted a rating and review for a program When the admin reviews my rating and review Then the admin should approve or reject the review based on guidelines And I should be notified if my review is published or rejected

testcase.classname: Monitor user activity and engagement statistics
